Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour the @water{200%ml}(for the rice) into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{100%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, add the @British Chicken Breasts{2} to a #medium bowl{}, drizzle with some @oil{} and sprinkle over the @Indonesian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat the chicken.

Lay the chicken onto one side of a #large baking tray{} and roast on the top shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, zest and cut the @Lime{1}(zested and cut into wedges) into wedges. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve any thick @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%g} stems lengthways.

When the chicken has 12 mins left, pop the Tenderstem® broccoli onto the other side of the #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

Return to the oven and roast until the broccoli is tender and crispy, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain the @King Prawns{150g}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the prawns. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir-fry for ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the garlic and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute} more.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. They're cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Stir the @Peas{120%g} into the prawns and heat until piping hot, ~{1%minute}.

Once the rice is cooked, fluff it up with a fork, then stir it into the prawns and peas. Mix in the @Soy Sauce{25%ml}, @Ketjap Manis{25%g} and @Honey{15%g}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, put the sachet in a bowl of hot water for 1 min to loosen.

Toss until well combined and fry for ~{1%minute} more, then remove from the heat.

Add a good squeeze of lime juice and the lime zest to the rice and toss. Taste and season with more lime juice, salt and pepper if needed.

Once cooked, cut the chicken widthways into 2cm thick slices. Transfer the chicken to your plates and drizzle over the @Sweet Chilli Sauce{48%g}.

Serve the prawn fried rice and broccoli alongside.

Finish with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!